/*
An string of words is given, the task is to reverse the string using stack.

Input Format:
The first line of input will contains an integer T denoting the no of test cases . Then T test cases follow. Each test case contains a
string s of words without spaces.

Output Format:
For each test case ,print the reverse of the string in new line. 

Your Task:
Since this is a function problem, you don't need to take any input. Just complete the provided function.

Constraints:
1 <= T <= 100
1 <= length of the string <= 100

Example:
Input:
2
GeeksQuiz
GeeksforGeeks
Output:
ziuQskeeG
skeeGrofskeeG
*/

void reverse(char *str, int len)
{
 stack<char> st;
 for(int i=0; i<len; i++){
     st.push(str[i]);
 }
 int i=0;
 while(!st.empty()){
     str[i++]=st.top();
     st.pop();
 }
}
